<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1891,2024]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,392]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,1927,1952]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[406,475,1927,1951]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1847,1870]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1823]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Belciades spp., imagines. 1, 2 – B. niveola (1 – Russian Far East, 2 – Korea); 3, 4 – B. koenigi, China (3 – holotype), 5, 6 – B. hoenei, China, (5 – holotype, 6 – paratype); 7, 8 – B. sugii (7 – Thailand, 8 – China)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203317/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[459,475,1927,1951]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[617,742,1927,1951]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.95" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="39.5" valueMax="43.0" valueMin="36.0">36–43 mm</quantity>
. The species is close to 
<taxonomicName box="[1013,1096,1928,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveola">
<emphasis box="[1013,1096,1928,1952]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">niveola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1151,1241,1928,1952]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName box="[1151,1237,1928,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koenigi">koenigi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Externally it differs in the grassy-green tint of ground color of forewing with less greyish suffusion, and in uniform greyish brown hindwing. In ground plan of forewing 
<taxonomicName box="[586,661,2000,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[586,661,2000,2024]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<emphasis box="[810,899,2000,2024]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName box="[810,895,2000,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveola">niveola</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
differing in shape of basal band, round whitish orbicular stigma, absence of whitish surrounding of inner and outer lines and grey suffusion in cell between orbicular and reniform stigmata. The medial shade is more distinct than in 
<taxonomicName box="[960,1043,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveola">
<emphasis box="[960,1043,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">niveola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1102,1185,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koenigi">
<emphasis box="[1102,1185,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">koenigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, lower part of medial field not suffused with dark grey as in 
<taxonomicName box="[598,681,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveola">
<emphasis box="[598,681,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">niveola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, subterminal and terminal fields with less brown suffusion. In the male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[329,413,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1774,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1753]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Belciades spp., male genitalia. 17 – B. niveola, Russian Far East, genit. prep. 1641 ZFMK; 18 – B. koenigi, paratype, China, genit. prep. 1641 ZFMK; 19 – B. hoenei, paratype, genit. prep. 1639 ZFMK; 20 – B. sugii, Thailand, genit. prep. 7277 GB." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203319/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
Fig. 
<number box="[384,413,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
) the species differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[711,793,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveola">
<emphasis box="[711,793,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">niveola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly in size and shape of valva, sacculus, uncus and juxta as well as in shape and armature of vesica. The female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[937,1017,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 26" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1841,1864]" captionTargetBox="[188,1415,194,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1821]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 26. Belciades spp., male and female genitalia. 21 – B. cyana, male genitalia, paratype, China, HHL- 1964 - 1; 22 – B. cyanobrunnea, male genitalia, holotype, Thailand, genit. prep. 7410 GB; 23 – B. niveola female genitalia, Russian Far East, genit. prep. 1641 ZFMK; 24 – B. koenigi female genitalia 1160 ZFMK; 25 – B. hoenei female genitalia, genit. prep. 1652 ZFMK; 26 – B. cyanobrunnea, paratype, female genitalia, China, Jianxi / Fujian, 7408 GB." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203320/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
Fig. 
<number box="[988,1017,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
) show more prominent differences in shape of bursa and ostial part.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
